<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 06 at 8:26PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southeastern Catawba,
southern Iredell and Rowan Counties through 900 PM EDT...
At 826 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 4 miles southwest of Statesville to near
Salisbury. Movement was southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Salisbury, Statesville, Kannapolis, Mooresville, China Grove,
Spencer, Landis, Enochville, Granite Quarry and Rockwell.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
